            <div type="textpart" n="1">
               <head xml:lang="eng">C. 86.1</head>
            <ab>
            <lb n="1"/> <g type="quatrefoil"/> madā pu pom̃ tana rayā sidaḥ yām̃ pom̃ ku śrī jaya
            <lb break="no" n="2"/>parameśvaravarmmadeva aum̃ aṅśarāja urām̃ turaiy· vijaya
            <lb n="3"/> di jam̃ḥ kaliḥ kamvuja ya 32 thun· nan· ra dr̥m̃ rājam̃ ekachatra
            <lb n="4"/> di nagara campa nī ra punaḥ sarvvaliṅga gaḥ dakṣiṇabhāga ma
            <lb break="no" n="5"/>kapun· yām̃ pu nagara ra punaḥ liṅga gaḥ uttarabhāga ma
            <lb break="no" n="6"/>kapun· yām̃ pom̃ k<unclear>u</unclear> śrīśānabhadreśvara pu po<unclear>m̃</unclear> ku
            <lb n="7"/> ra vuḥ raupyakośa suvarṇṇamukha ṅan· kośa 
            <lb n="8"/> <unclear>yā</unclear>m̃ bhr̥uguḥ maddan· sarvvabhogopabhoga māḥ ṅa
            <lb break="no" n="9"/>n· <unclear>pira</unclear>k· samudāya yauṁ sa ratuḥ thil· māḥ 
            <lb n="10"/> kāla śakarāja 1156 <g type="quatrefoil"/> <g>|</g>
            </ab>
         </div>   
         
             <div type="textpart" n="2">
                <head xml:lang="eng">C. 86.2</head>
                <ab>
            <lb n="1"/> <g type="quatrefoil"/> nī mula dravya pom̃ pu lakim̃ kālāntakatha <gap reason="lost" quantity="4" unit="character"/>
            <lb break="no" n="2"/>nandana urām̃ mvlām̃ vijaya vuḥ pak· yām̃ pom̃ ku śrī<supplied reason="lost">ānabhadre</supplied>
            <lb break="no" n="3"/>śvara pu pom̃ ku limān· vinai sā klauṅ· māḥ sā 3 th<supplied reason="lost">il· ca</supplied>
            <lb break="no" n="4"/>lāhvaya pirak· sā 20 thil<unclear>·</unclear> pralauṅ· pirak· sā 2<supplied reason="lost">0 thil·</supplied>
            <lb n="5"/> vraḥ o<supplied reason="lost">ṁ</supplied>kāra sā sā thil· māḥ matā dhunī sā si vuḥ ganan·
            <lb n="6"/> yauṁ sā thil· māḥ pirak· kakai nan· 2 thil· pranīṅ· 1
            <lb n="7"/> yauṁ 2 thil· māḥ kaṅsabhāja 2 bhāja laṅguv· 1 vadala
            <lb n="8"/> 2 svam̃n· 1 kvir· 1 lakiy· 1 krumviy· 1152 <g type="quatrefoil"/>
                </ab>
             </div>
         </div><div type="apparatus"><!-- AL: it will be nicer to get the apparatus after the first part of the text, not at the end of the whole text--><div type="textpart"><head xml:lang="eng">C. 86.1</head><listApp><app loc="2"><lem>aum̃ aṅśarāja</lem><note><bibl><ptr target="bib:Finot1904_05"/><citedRange unit="page">976</citedRange></bibl> added a note: <quote>on pourrait aussi bien lire Saṅgarāja; mais la comparaison de Po nagar 409, B,4 <supplied reason="explanation"><ref target="C0030B4.xml">C. 30 B4</ref></supplied> ligne 2, où l’écriture est plus nette, montre que la vraie forme est Aṅçarāja</quote>.</note></app><app loc="5"><lem>ra punaḥ liṅga</lem><rdg source="bib:Finot1904_05">ra punaḥ sarvvaliṅga</rdg></app><app loc="9"><lem>yauṁ</lem><rdg source="bib:Finot1904_05">yoṁ</rdg></app></listApp></div><div type="textpart"><head xml:lang="eng">C. 86.2</head><listApp><app loc="1"><lem>nī</lem><rdg source="bib:Finot1904_05">ni</rdg></app><app loc="3"><lem>śrī<supplied reason="lost">ānabhadre</supplied>śvara</lem><note>Reconstitution of Finot</note></app><app loc="3"><lem>sā</lem><rdg source="bib:Finot1904_05">sa</rdg></app><app loc="4"><lem><supplied reason="lost">ca</supplied>lāhvaya</lem><note>one would also find this world in <ref target="DHARMA_INSCIC00006.xml">C. 6</ref>, l. 2.</note></app><app loc="8"><lem>svam̃n</lem><rdg source="bib:Finot1904_05">svãḥ</rdg></app><app loc="8"><lem>kvir</lem><rdg source="bib:Finot1904_05">kvir̥</rdg><note>It must be a typo.</note></app></listApp></div></div><!-- AL: <div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
           <div type="textpart" n="1">
             <head xml:lang="en">C. 86.1</head>
             <p>There was a P.P.T.R., namely Y.P.K. Śrī Jayaparameśvaravarmadeva oṅ Aṅśarāja, person of Turaiy Vijaya. Following this 32-year "war" against Cambodia, he <supplied reason="explanation">the sovereign</supplied> ruled over this Campā kingdom with the unique umbrella.
            He restored all the <foreign>liṅga</foreign> of the Southern side namely [these of] Yām̃ Pu Nagara; he restored <foreign>liṅga</foreign> of the Northern side namely [these of] Y.P.K. Īśanabhadreśvara P.P.K. 
            He offered a silver <foreign>kośa</foreign> with a golden face and a <foreign>kośa</foreign> to the Bhr̥uguḥ deity with all golden and silver goods and means of subsistence for a total amount of one hundred <foreign>thil</foreign> of gold, in the year of the Śaka king 1156.</p>
           /div>
           <div type="textpart" n="2">
             <head xml:lang="en">C. 86.2</head>
             <p>This [is] the (furniture/movable??) capital offered by the P.P. homme Kālāntakatha (...) nandana, person of Mvlām̃ Vijaya, to Y.P.K. Śrī Īśanabhadreśvara P.P.K.: a female elephant, a small golden box (<foreign>klauṅ</foreign>): 3 <foreign>thil</foreign>; a silver<foreign>calāhvaya</foreign>: 20 <foreign>thil</foreign>; 
            a silver neckless: 20 <foreign>thil</foreign>; a Holy <foreign>oṁkāra</foreign>: one <foreign>thil</foreign> of gold; a precious stone <foreign>dhunī</foreign> given <foreign>ganan</foreign> of a value of one <foreign>thil</foreign> of gold; this silver for the tripod: 2 <foreign>thil</foreign>; 
            <foreign>pranīṅ</foreign>: 1 of a value of 2 <foreign>thil</foreign> of  gold; vases (made) of copper: 2; vase (made) of cuprous metal: 1; <foreign>vadala</foreign>: 2; <foreign>svam̃n</foreign>: 1; Khmer: 1 man; 1 woman. [In Śaka] 1152.</p>
           /div>
         </div> --><div type="translation" xml:lang="fra"><div type="textpart" n="1"><head xml:lang="eng">C. 86.1</head><p>Il y eut un P.P.T.R., à savoir Y.P.K. Śrī Jayaparameśvaravarmadeva oṅ Aṅśarāja, personne de Turaiy Vijaya. À la suite de cette “guerre” du Cambodge qui <supplied reason="subaudible">dura</supplied> 32 ans, il <supplied reason="explanation">le souverain</supplied> gouverna avec le parasol unique sur ce royaume du Campā. 
                  Il restaura tous les <foreign>liṅga</foreign> du côté Sud à savoir <supplied reason="subaudible">ceux de</supplied> Yām̃ Pu Nagara; il restaura les <foreign>liṅga</foreign> du côté Nord à savoir <supplied reason="subaudible">ceux de</supplied> Y.P.K. Īśanabhadreśvara P.P.K. 
                  Il offrit un <foreign>kośa</foreign> d’argent avec un visage en or et un <foreign>kośa</foreign> à la divinité Bhr̥guḥ avec tous les biens et les moyens de subsistance d’or et d’argent pour une valeur totale de cent <foreign>thil</foreign> d’or, en l’année 1156 du roi des Śaka.</p></div><div type="textpart" n="2"><head xml:lang="eng">C. 86.2</head><p>Ceci <supplied reason="subaudible">est</supplied> le capital mobilier offert par le P.P. homme Kālāntakatha (...) nandana, personne de Mvlām̃ Vijaya, à Y.P.K. Śrī Īśanabhadreśvara P.P.K.: une éléphante, une petite boîte (<foreign>klauṅ</foreign>) d’or: 3 <foreign>thil</foreign>; un <foreign>calāhvaya</foreign> en argent: 20 <foreign>thil</foreign>; 
               un collier d’argent: 20 <foreign>thil</foreign>; un saint <foreign>oṁkāra</foreign>: un <foreign>thil</foreign> d’or; une pierre précieuse <foreign>dhunī</foreign> donnée <foreign>ganan</foreign> d’une valeur d’un <foreign>thil</foreign> d’or; cet argent pour le (tré)pied: 2 <foreign>thil</foreign>; 
               <foreign>pranīṅ</foreign>: 1 d’une valeur de 2 <foreign>thil</foreign> d’or; vases de cuivre: 2; vase de métal cuivreux: 1; <foreign>vadala</foreign>: 2; <foreign>svam̃n</foreign>: 1; Khmers: 1 homme; 1 femme. <supplied reason="subaudible">En Śaka</supplied> 1152.</p></div></div><!--  <div type="commentary">
            <p>In ancient Cam, <foreign>yauṁ</foreign> means "about, more or less". In modern Cam, it could mean "(money) value, price". The comparison with <ref target="DHARMA_INSCIC00184.xml">C. 184</ref> where the figure 158 follows the occurrence, suggests that the translation "value" is more appropriate than "more or less".</p>
            <p><foreign>pralauṅ</foreign> = <foreign>pralaum̃</foreign> = <foreign>pralauv</foreign>. In <bibl><ptr target="cic-bibl= Aymonier &amp; Cabaton 1906"/></bibl>, the word <foreign>pralau</foreign> is repertoried. The authors drew a parallel between this term and the one one could find in Khmer which means "neckless".</p>
            <p>Concerning the meaning of <foreign>calāhvaya</foreign>, see the note for this occurrence in the inscription <ref target="C.0006.xml">C. 6</ref>, l. 2.</p>
            <p>Finot translated <foreign>kaṅsabhāja</foreign> "copper vase".</p>
            <p>Finot translated <foreign>bhāja laṅguv</foreign> "earthen vase".</p>
         </div> --><div type="bibliography"><p>First published, with French translation, in <bibl><ptr target="bib:Finot1904_05"/><citedRange unit="page">976-977</citedRange></bibl>; whence C. 86.2 was summed up and C. 86.1 was translated into English in <bibl><ptr target="bib:Majumdar1985_01"/><citedRange unit="page">207-208</citedRange></bibl>; <bibl><ptr target="bib:Golzio2004_01"/><citedRange unit="page">178</citedRange></bibl> read and translated both. The present edition and translation after <bibl><ptr target="bib:Lepoutre2013_01"/><citedRange unit="page">264-265</citedRange></bibl>.</p><listBibl type="primary"><bibl/></listBibl><listBibl type="secondary"><bibl><ptr target="bib:Parmentier1909_01"/><citedRange unit="page">381-382</citedRange></bibl><bibl><ptr target="bib:Griffiths+al2008-2009_01"/><citedRange unit="page">456 and 458</citedRange></bibl></listBibl></div></body></text>
